BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Band Tonight! The Western Elstons
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20200314T010000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20200314T040000Z
UID:6p2a21upd98uqkkkmghcf7euka@google.com
DESCRIPTION:The Western Elstons have been playing at the historic Simon's 
 Tavern in the Andersonville neighborhood of Chicago for over ten years now
 . They play country\, honky tonk\, and rock & roll with minimal amplificat
 ion to an appreciative crowd of regulars and local music fans. The Western
  Elstons feature the tight two-part harmony of Scott Ligon and Casey McDon
 ough (who play and sing together in countless projects including NRBQ and 
 The Flat Five)\, masterful guitar by Joel Patterson (Devil in a Woodpile\,
  The Modern Sounds\, Organ Trio with Chris Foreman)\, and the always taste
 ful drumming of Alex Hall (also in The Flat Five\, The Modern Sounds\, The
  Fat Babies\, and many more).
X-SOURCE:Evanston American Legion
END:VEVENT
